  "prompt": "I got placed in TCS's EIS stream in my campus placement. Will I get a job in EIS or in IT?",
  "response": "Congratulations on your placement in TCS's EIS (Enterprise Intelligent Solutions) stream! Generally, if you have been placed in the EIS stream, you are expected to work within that domain. EIS is a specialized area focusing on enterprise solutions, which may include roles related to data analytics, enterprise architecture, or other intelligent solutions.\n\nHowever, in practice, the exact nature of your job can depend on various factors, including the specific needs of the company at the time of your joining, the projects they are working on, and your skills or interests. While you may primarily be hired for EIS, there could be opportunities to work on IT-related projects as well.\n\nIt's a good idea to clarify your role and responsibilities with HR or your manager once you join to get a clearer picture of what to expect. Good luck in your new role!",
